## 1. The HDB binary is NOT redistributed

The Project decodes the `XFILES.HDB` data file shipped with the 1997 game
*The X-Files: The Game*. The data file `XFILES.HDB` is the
intellectual property of its publisher and is **not** redistributed by this
Project. Users must legally possess a copy of the game to apply the decoder.

The Project does not contain any game asset (video, audio, text, image,
script). All test fixtures use either synthetic data or empirical checksums.

## 2. NeoPersist 3.0 reference headers

The directory `headers/neopersist_3.0/` contains 13 C++ header files plus
`CNeoStream.cp` and `NeoAccess.cp`. These were authored by NeoLogic Systems
Inc. between 1992 and 1996 and were publicly distributed as part of the
CodeWarrior 7 SDK (Metrowerks, ~1996) and inside the *Doom for Macintosh*
source code release (id Software).

They are included here verbatim, **without modification**, for the sole
purpose of interoperability — specifically, to allow developers to verify
and extend the byte-direct decoder against the original API contract.
Their inclusion is in keeping with the interoperability provisions of
17 U.S.C. § 1201(f) (DMCA, USA), Article 6 of Directive 2009/24/EC
(Computer Programs Directive, EU), and equivalent statutes elsewhere.

If you are the copyright holder of these files and prefer they be removed,
please open an issue and they will be deleted promptly.

See `headers/neopersist_3.0/NOTICE.md` for file-by-file provenance.

